# Storybook MCP Workflow

This project has a Storybook MCP server at `http://localhost:6006/mcp` when Storybook is running.

## Before touching any component

1. Call `list-all-documentation` to discover what exists.
2. Call `get-documentation` for the specific component -- read the actual prop interface. **Never guess props.**
3. If a prop isn't in the documentation, it doesn't exist. Ask the user before inventing one.

## Before writing or editing stories

1. Call `get-storybook-story-instructions` to get current project conventions.
2. Follow CSF3 format: `Meta<typeof Component>` + `StoryObj` + named exports.
3. Set `title` to match folder hierarchy: `'Atoms/Button'`, `'Molecules/Card'`, `'Organisms/Navbar'`, `'Pages/Dashboard'`.
4. Always include a `Default` story with realistic, production-like props.
5. Use `args` for controllable stories, `render` for multi-variant showcases.
6. Add play functions for interactive behavior (dismiss, submit, sort, toggle).

## After any change

1. Call `run-story-tests` to run interaction tests + accessibility checks.
2. Fix all failures before considering the task done.
3. Call `preview-stories` to generate a visual preview.

## Styling rules

- Use CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) consuming tokens from `src/tokens/design-tokens.css`.
- Reference tokens as `var(--color-primary-500)`, `var(--space-4)`, etc.
- Never hardcode colors, spacing, or radii -- always use token variables.

## Component placement

| Level | Folder | Examples |
|-------|--------|----------|
| Atoms | `src/components/atoms/` | Button, Input, Badge, Avatar, Toggle |
| Molecules | `src/components/molecules/` | Card, Alert, Tooltip, SearchBar |
| Organisms | `src/components/organisms/` | Navbar, Sidebar, DataTable, Form |
| Pages | `src/components/pages/` | LoginPage, Dashboard |

New components go in a folder with three files: `Name.tsx`, `Name.module.css`, `Name.stories.tsx`.
